                                <p class="">Customer Limited Liabbility Protection Policy (Unauthorized Electronic Payment Transactions)</p>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Introduction :</li>
                                        <p class="p-0">Appnit Technologies Private Limited (hereinafter referred as “Hellope”) is committed to provide superior and safe customer service experience to all its customers. To enable the above, Hellope has over the years invested in technology and has robust security systems and fraud detection and preventions mechanisms in place to ensure safe and secure payments experience to its customers. As entailed in the Citizen’s charter, Hellope already has in place policies such as Privacy Policy.</p>
                                        <p class="p-0">Keeping in mind the increasing thrust on financial inclusion & customer protection, the Reserve Bank of India had issued a circular on Customer Protection – Limiting Liability of Customers in Unauthorised Electronic Payment Transactions. (RBI/2018-19/101 DPSS.CO.PD.No.1417/ 02.14.006/2018 – 19 dated January 04, 2019) which inter-alia requires Non Banks Prepaid Payment Instrument Issuers to formulate a Board approved policy in regard to customer protection and compensation in case of unauthorized electronic payment transactions</p>
                                    <li>Objective :</li>
                                    <p>This policy seeks to communicate in a fair and transparent manner Hellope’s policy on:</p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Customer protection (including mechanism of creating customer awareness on the risks andresponsibilities involved in electronic payment transactions),</li>
                                        <li>Customer liability in cases of unauthorized electronic payment transactions</li>
                                        <li>Customer compensation due to unauthorized electronic payment transactions (within defined timelines)</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    <li class="py-2">Scope :</li>
                                    <p class="p-0">The electronic payment transactions can be broadly divided into two categories:</p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Remote/ online payment transactions: Transactions that do not require physical payment instruments to be presented at the point of transactions e.g. internet banking, mobile banking, card not present (CNP)transactions, Pre-paid Payment Instruments (PPI), and</li>
                                        <li>Face-to-face/ proximity payment transactions: Transactions which require the physical payment instrument such as a card or mobile phone to be present at the point of transaction e.g. ATM, POS, etc.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    <li class="py-2">Applicability:</li>
                                    <p class="p-0"><b>1 .</b> This policy is applicable to entities that hold relationship with Hellope viz.:</p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Individual and non-individual customers who hold current or savings account.</li>
                                        <li> Individual / non-individual entities that hold credit card and/or prepaid card.</li>
                                        <li>Individual / non-individual entities using other electronic platforms of Hellopewallet.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    <p class="py-2 m-0"><b>2 .</b> This policy is not applicable to:</p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Non-Customer that use Bank’s infrastructure e.g. ATMs etc.</li>
                                        <li>Entities that are part of the ecosystem such as Interchange organisations, Franchises, Intermediaries,Agencies, Service partners, Vendors, Merchants etc.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    <li class="py-2">Liability of the Customer:</li>
                                    <p class="p-0">Customer shall be compensated in line with this policy in case of loss occurring due to unauthorizedtransaction as follows:</p>

                                    <ol>
                                        <li class="py-2">Zero Liability of a Customer:</li>
                                        <ol>
                                            <li>Customer shall be entitled to full compensation of real loss in the event of contributory fraud/negligence/ deficiency on the part of Hellope (irrespective of whether or not the transaction is reportedby the customer).</li>
                                            <li>Customer has Zero Liability in all cases of third party breach where the deficiency lies neither with Hellope nor with the customer but lies elsewhere in the system and the customer notifies Hellope within three working days of receiving the communication from Hellope regarding the unauthorised transaction.</li>
                                        </ol>
                                        <li class="py-2">Limited Liability of customer:</li>
                                        <ol>
                                            <li>In cases where the loss is due to negligence by a customer, such as where he has shared the payment credentials, the customer will bear the entire loss until he reports the unauthorized transaction to the Hellope. Any loss occurring after the reporting of the unauthorized transaction shall be borne by Hellope.</li>
                                            <li>In cases where the responsibility for the unauthorized electronic payment transaction lies neither with Hellope nor with the customer, but lies elsewhere in the system and there is a delay on the part of customer in notifying/reporting to the Hellope beyond 3 working days and less than or equal to 7 working days (after receiving the intimation from Hellope), the liability of the customer per transactionshall be limited to transaction value or amounts mentioned in Annexure -1 whichever is lower.</li>
                                        </ol>
                                        <li class="py-2">Complete Liability of customer:</li>
                                        <ol>
                                            <li>Customer shall bear the entire loss in cases where the loss is due to negligence by the customer, e.g. where the customer has shared the payment credentials or Account/Transaction details, viz. Hellope user Id & PIN, OTP or due to improper protection on customer devices like laptop2/ desktop leading to malware/Trojan or Phishing attack. <br>Under such situations, the customer will bear the entire loss until the customer reports unauthorised transaction to Hellope. Any loss occurring after reporting of unauthorised transaction shall be borne byHellope.</li>
                                            <li>In cases where the responsibility for unauthorized electronic payment transaction lies neither withHellope nor with the customer but lies elsewhere in the system and when there is a delay on the part of the customer in reporting to Hellope beyond 7 working days, the customer would be completely liable for all such transactions.</li>
                                        </ol>
                                    </ol>
                                    <li class="py-2">Reversal Time line for Zero Liability/ Limited Liability of customer:</li>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Hellope shall credit (shadow reversal) the amount involved in the unauthorized electronic transaction <br>to the customer’s account within 10 working days from the date of such notification by the customer.</li>
                                        <li>Within 90 days of the date of reporting, Hellope shall either establish customer negligence or provide final credit to the customer. In case Hellope in unable to resolve the complaint or determine customer liability, if any, within 90 days, the amount as prescribed in clause 5.2 above shall be paid to customer, irrespective of whether negligence is on Your part or otherwise.</li>
                                        <li>Hellope may, at its discretion, agree to credit the customer even in case of an established negligenceby the customer.</li>
                                        <li>Customer would not be entitled to compensation of loss if any, in case customer does not agree to cooperate with the Hellope by providing necessary documents, as requested, including the police complaint etc.</li>
                                        <li>Compensation would be limited to the real loss after deduction of reversals or recoveries received by the customer.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    <li class="py-2">Third Party Breach</li>
                                    <p class="py-3">The following would be considered as Third party breach where deficiency lies neither with Hellope norcustomer but elsewhere in the system:</p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Application frauds</li>
                                        <li>Account takeover</li>
                                        <li>Skimming / cloning</li>
                                        <li>External frauds / compromise of other systems, for e.g. ATMs / mail servers etc. being compromised</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    <li class="py-2">Roles & Responsibilities of Hellope:</li>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Hellope shall ensure that the Customer protection policy is available on Hellope’s website/mobileApp for the reference by customers.</li>
                                        <li>Hellope shall also ensure that existing customers are individually informed about Hellope’s policy.</li>
                                        <li>Hellope will regularly conduct awareness on carrying out safe electronic payment transactions to itscustomers and staff. Such information will include rights and obligation of the customers as well as non-disclosure of sensitive information e.g. password, PIN, OTP, date of birth, etc</li>
                                        <li>Hellope shall communicate to its customers to mandatorily register for SMS alerts. Hellope will send SMS alerts to all valid registered mobile number for all debit electronic payment transactions. Hellope may also send alert by email where email Id has been registered with Hellope.</li>
                                        <li>For reporting of unauthorized transactions, the customers may refer to the “Customer Grievance Redressal Mechanism” of the Customer</li>
                                        <li>Hellope shall respond to customer’s notification of unauthorized electronic payment transaction with acknowledgment specifying the date and time of receipt of customer’s notification.</li>
                                        <li>On receipt of customer’s notification, Hellope will take immediate steps to prevent further unauthorized electronic payment transactions in the account..</li>
                                        <li>Hellope shall ensure that all such complaints are resolved and liability of customer if any, establishedwithin a maximum of 90 days from the date of receipt of complaint, failing which, Hellope would pay compensation as described in Annexure 1.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                </ol>
                            </ol>
